Groceries like sanitisers and toilet paper are flying off the shelves at several supermarkets. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - As the spread of the coronavirus continues, several people in South Africa have headed to supermarkets on Monday to stock up on goods. SUMMARY: Ramaphosa announces COVID-19 controls Groceries like sanitisers and toilet paper are flying off the shelves as people prepare for the possibility of self-isolation. President Cyril Ramaphosa on Sunday announced several measures that will be implemented to reduce the impact of the virus.  